  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: On first run syncing started from block X (655359) and is 100% done on block Y (731652 ). Than app is closed, opened again, user logs in -> syncing again starts from the same block X (655359).\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nSyncing starts from the last synced block Y\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nOn second run syncing starts from the same block as on first run (block X).\r\nNote: on third run sync starts from the expected block (last synced block of the second run)\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Install Status and create a password for new account\r\n- Note the block where syncing starts. In console use web3.eth.blockNumber to see the block number when sync starts and when sync is 100%\r\n- Close app\r\n- Run app again and log in\r\n- Open Console and web3.eth.blockNumber \r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.5\r\n* Operating System: iOs 10.2.1\r\n\r\n",
